03057nmm a2200481Ia 9780520914865DE-B159720240326120151.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240326t20231994cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209148657 a10.1525/97805209148652doi  a(DE-B1597)543291  a(OCoLC)1163878603  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aDS707b.I57 1994eb 7aLIT0080002bisacsh04a95122000aInscribed Landscapes :bTravel Writing from Imperial China.  aReprint 2019 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2023] 4cÂ©1994  a1 online resource (489 p.) :b1 frontisp.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAlongside the scores of travel books about China written by foreign visitors, Chinese travelers' impressions of their own country rarely appear in translation. This anthology is the only comprehensive collection in English of Chinese travel writing from the first century A.D. through the nineteenth. Early examples of the genre describe sites important for their geography, history, and role in cultural mythology, but by the T'ang dynasty in the mid-eighth century certain historiographical and poetic discourses converged to form the "travel account" (yu-chi) and later the "travel diary" (jih-chi) as vehicles of personal expression and autobiography. These first-person narratives provide rich material for understanding the attitudes of Chinese literati toward place, nature, politics, and the self.The anthology is abundantly illustrated with paintings, portraits, maps, and drawings. Each selection is meticulously translated, carefully annotated, and prefaced by a brief description of the writer's life and work. The entire collection is introduced by an in-depth survey of the rise of Chinese travel writing as a cultural phenomenon. Inscribed Landscapes provides a unique resource for travelers as well as for scholars of Chinese literature, art, and history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh1 aStrassberg, Richard E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520914865?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520914865423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520914865/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles